dataSetInformation.common:name: Eutrophication marine
dataSetInformation.impactIndicator: Fraction of nutrients reaching marine end compartment (N)
dataSetInformation.common:generalComment: European validity. Averaged characterization factors from country dependent characterization factors.

geography.geographicalRepresentativenessDescriptio: Valid for Europe (averaged factors based on country-dependent assessments).

impactModel.modelName: CARMEN model for waterborne emissions and EUTREND for airborne emissions.
impactModel.modelDescription: The exposure factors for water-borne emissions are Calculated using the CARMEN model. For air-borne emissions, the exposure factors are Calculated with EUTREND. Only impacts on marine systems are considered in this model.
impactModel.consideredMechanisms: Inclusion of important removal mechanisms for N (limiting nutrient).

modellingAndValidation.useAdviceForDataSet: Representative for Europe. Averaged characterization factor data set (from country-dependent assessments).

review.common:reviewDetails: Methods and characterization factors are well documented and accessible for use. Models and input data not easily accessible. High environmental relevance with consideration of removal processes. Overall, the models for European conditions address all aspects of aquatic eutrophication for both water-borne and air-borne emissions. Moderate stakeholder acceptance. Overall good quality and good applicability of the factors (based on country-dependent assessment) at the European scale. Models potentially adaptable to generate characteriation factors for other continents if complemented by appropriate fate models.

common:referenceToNameOfReviewerAndInsti.common:shortDescription: Consortium for defining the recommended Life Cycle Impact Assessment framework, methods and factors

common:referenceToCompleteReviewReport.common:shortDescription: Review report on recommended LCIA methods

common:referenceToCommissioner.common:shortDescription: Ministry of Housing, Spatial Planning and Environment (VROM)

common:commissionerAndGoal.common:project: LCIA method original development within the ReCiPe project (see www.lcia-recipe.net/) based on EUTREND model (Struijs et al 2009) . Documentation as ILCD formatted data set, mapping to the ILCD elementary flows, and additional quality checks by the ECâ€™s JRC-IES and with contractual support projects, partly financed under several Administrative Arrangements on the European Platform on LCA - EPLCA' between JRC and DG ENV, (070402/2006/443456/G4, 070307/2007/474521/G4, 070307/2008/513489/G4).
common:commissionerAndGoal.common:intendedApplications: Provide applicable midpoint characterization factors for marine eutrophication in Europe.

publicationAndOwnership.common:accessRestrictions: The data set can be used free of charge by anybody to perform LCA studies, to distribute it to third parties, to convert it to other formats, to develop own data sets etc. as long as the copyright and license conditions for the ELCD data sets and the ILCD format are met that can be accessed via http://lca.jrc.ec.europa.eu and are part of the ELCD database distribution package. Please note e.g. that reference must be given to the 'Owner of data set' (who may have additional copyright and license requirements on the particular data set that are to be met) and to the 'ELCD database' plus version number, when using the data set or parts thereof. Please note also that any modifications/omissions of the data set results in invalidity of any existing 'Official recommendation of data set by governmental body', that the impression must be avoided that this would still be an original ELCD data set, and that the content of further fields may have to be adjusted. For details see the aforementioned copyright and license conditions as well as those the 'Owner of data set' may have put into force.
